    "course_title": "MATHEMATICAL TECHNIQUES IN THE ANALYSIS OF ALGORITHMS",
    "description": "Techniques for quantitative analysis of algorithms. Charging arguments, amortization, probabilistic methods. Adversary and information lower bounds. Use of methods from combinatorics, complex analysis, and asymptotics in obtaining precise analyses of quicksort, chained hashing, and other algorithms.  Students are strongly encouraged to have knowledge of algorithms (e.g.,COMP\u00a0SCI\u00a0577) or applied math analysis (e.g.,MATH\u00a0321) and theory of probability (e.g.,MATH/\u200bSTAT\u00a0\u00a0431).",
